request.description:
Poll this endpoint every 2-3 seconds after calling POST /recording/prepare to check if the recording is ready.

**Response statuses:**
- `{"status": "processing"}` — Still downloading/uploading, keep polling
- `{"status": "ready", "url": "https://storage.googleapis.com/...signed...", "download_url": "https://storage.googleapis.com/...signed..."}` — Recording ready. Use `url` as <audio src> for streaming playback (supports seeking). Use `download_url` in an <a href download> for saving the file.
- `{"status": "failed", "error": "Recording not yet available from Vobiz"}` — Pipeline failed, show error to user
- `{"status": "not_started"}` — prepare was never called for this call_id

**Frontend usage:**
```js
// Poll until ready
const poll = setInterval(async () => {
  const res = await fetch(`/api/analytics/${callId}/recording/status`);
  const data = await res.json();
  if (data.status === 'ready') {
    clearInterval(poll);
    audioElement.src = data.url; // streaming playback
    // data.download_url available for download button
  } else if (data.status === 'failed') {
    clearInterval(poll);
    showError(data.error);
  }
}, 3000);
```

**Notes:**
- Status is stored in Redis with 30min TTL matching the signed URL expiry
- After TTL expires, status returns not_started and prepare must be called again
- Both url and download_url are GCS signed URLs valid for 30 minutes
